            "answer_text": "No \u2014 in fact, it\u2019s arguable that telling a lie (which is not exactly the same thing as honesty but overlaps quite extensively) is the *paradigmatically* immoral act, insofar as it intentionally misrepresents one\u2019s own deliberative process. Since duty involves identifying those maxims upon which all of us ought to act, to misrepresent the maxims that we ourselves are acting on is always immoral. ",
